First off, we would like to apologize for not being able to conduct the
first session as planned.

The first session - *Introduction to R - *will happen this Thursday.

Also, please fill this form <https://goo.gl/forms/ST4UIgik8vNTZeLh2> if you
are interested in attending this session and wish to be notified about
upcoming sessions.

R is a language that is very useful in data analysis, especially for
beginners, that is very easy to learn and use. In this session we will get
you started with R touching upon the basic syntax and common functions. We
will also go through some data sets and perform basic operations on them.

Date : *29/09/2016*
Day : *Thursday*
Venue : *CRC 102*
Time : *8:30 PM - 10:30 PM*

We will be working out everything in R. If you don't have R, use the
following links to download and install R
<https://cran.r-project.org/bin/windows/base/> and Rstudio
<https://www.rstudio.com/products/rstudio/download/> before you come to the
session.

Install the following packages in R or R Studio by typing the following
commands:

*install.packages("swirl")*
*install.packages("MASS")*
*install.packages("ISLR")*

Come with your laptops charged !!

